
Autorenewal of SSL Certificates:

To check status - sudo systemctl status certbot.timer

To List timers of certbot - sudo systemctl list-timers --all|grep certbot

To check status of nginx service - sudo systemctl status nginx




Check auto-renewal timer - systemctl list-timers

Enable certbot timer - sudo systemctl enable --now certbot.timer

Test renewal - sudo certbot renew --dry-run

Reload nginx after renew - Script in sudo nano /etc/letsencrypt/renewal-hooks/deploy/reload-nginx.sh

#!/bin/bash
systemctl reload nginx

After this, to make it executable :

sudo chmod +x /etc/letsencrypt/renewal-hooks/deploy/reload-nginx.sh

Verify certificates - sudo certbot certificates
